17 making loans in the same office or place of business as any other business. (NRS
18 675.230) Section 4 of this bill similarly exempts Internet consumer lenders from
19 those provisions.
20 Section 1 of this bill requires any contract between an Internet consumer lender
21 and a resident of this State for the provision of a loan to: (1) provide that the
22 contract is governed by the laws of this State; and (2) require that any process for
23 the resolution of disputes arising out of the contract occur in this State. Under
24 section 1, any condition, stipulation or provision in such a contract that conflicts
25 with such requirements is contrary to public policy and is void and unenforceable.
