1 Section 1. Chapter 675 of NRS is hereby amended by adding
2 thereto a new section to read as follows:
3 1. To the extent not preempted by federal law, any contract
4 between an Internet consumer lender and a resident of this State
5 for the provision of a loan must:
6 (a) Provide that the contract is governed by the laws of this
7 State; and
8 (b) Require that any litigation, arbitration or other process for
9 the resolution of disputes arising out of the contract occur in this
10 State.
11 2. Any condition, stipulation or provision in a contract
12 between an Internet consumer lender and a resident of this State
13 for the provision of a loan that conflicts with the provisions of this
14 section is contrary to public policy and is void and unenforceable.
